ncluding healthcare he has been a director of mariner health care inc since may   he has been the chairman at m iii acquisition corp since august   he serves as a director of anvil knitwear inc he is a director of the children’s museum of manhattan as well as the equity group international foundation mr meghji served on the board of directors of cascade timberlands llc from  to  he served as director of ms resorts from january  to february  he served as director of dan river inc previously he served on the board of healthright international from  to  from may  to december  he served on the board of directors of mariner health care management company mr meghji has more than  years of business and restructuring experience focused primarily on reviving companies experiencing financial operational or strategic transitions to maximize value for stakeholders he is a uk and canadian chartered accountant mr meghji graduated with a bachelor of business administration from the schulich school of business of york university canada in  and has completed the advanced corporate finance program at the insead business school in franceread full background corporate headquarters  columbus circlenew york new york united statesphone fax  board members memberships presentdirectormariner health care incpresentchairman  ceom iii acquisition corp education unknownother education inseadbba the schulich school of business york university other affiliations medical staffing network holdings incmariner health care incinseadonemain holdings incspringleaf finance corporationthe schulich school of business york universityloughlin management partnerscomiii partners llc annual compensation there is no annual compensation data available stocks options there is no stock options data available total compensation there is no total compensation data available request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of